==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dak
<hw>Dak</hw> <pr>(d⟦add⟧k <it>or</it> d⟦aum⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Hind. <ets>⟦dsdot⟧⟦amac⟧k</ets>.]</ety> <def>Post; mail; also, the
mail or postal arrangements; -- spelt also <asp>dawk</asp>, and
<asp>dauk</asp>.</def> <mark>[India]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Dak boat</b></col>, <cd>a mail boat.</cd> <au>Percy
Smith.</au> -- <col><b>Dak bungalow</b></col>, <cd>a traveler's
rest-house at the end of a dak stage.</cd> -- <col><b>To travel by
dak</b></col>, <cd>to travel by relays of palanquins or other carriage,
as fast as the post along a road.</cd></cs></p>

<p><ent>Dakar</ent>⟦br⟧
